com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: Jenkins Restarted
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description: Jenkins restarted during the running of this Build. If your Build failed after this message with no other errors then please update your branch and try running again. Your branch may need to be unlocked in BitBucket, please raise a Support Ticket with the Skynet team.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: Issues happening since OCP4 Migration

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: DataStage Object Locked
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description: DataStage asset (object) is currently locked and cannot be overwritten. Please check DataStage to see who has the object opened. Close object before attempting to deploy again.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: This happens when someone has the object opened for editing or viewing in DataStage, usually when a team is developing and forget to close it before deploying via the Pipeline. If this happens in DEV01 it indicates the team is using DEV01 to develop, which they shouldn't be doing.

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.pattern: .*(The asset is currently locked and cannot be overwritten).*

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: BT ET File in Wrong Folder
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description: The pipeline failed to execute the ET (END TRANSACTION) statement due to how teradata/one-off .sql files are handled. Please move the file to the teradata/dml folder and try again.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: Move file to the dml folder and try again.

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: Teradata Error
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description: Teradata JDBC Driver Error, please restart.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: Teradata Error, restart

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: Unable to Create Drivetrain Build
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description:
The pipeline was unable to create a new Drivetrain build.

Please advise the Skynet team of this issue and they will reach out to the Drivetrain team to resolve.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: Early in the pipeline run, when trying to create a new Drivetrain build over the API, the attempt fails, returning a HTTP 405 error. This error indicates an issue on the Drivetrain side and the only way to resolve it is to reach out to the Drivetrain team to get it restarted.

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: Branch Already Running

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: User error, running multiple builds with the same branch.

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.pattern: .*(build failed due to existing running build).*

com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description: The Connection to Artifactory failed. Please wait a few minutes then restart your Pipeline.
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.comment: Connection to Artifactory failed, please try again. Connectivity Issues with Artifactory. Please wait 10-30min then try again. We are looking into this. Needs to be looked into. Could be something to do with the DDoS attack that happened on the 8th of September 2021.
